dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Projected Coordinate System:

Projected Coordinate System:NAD_1983_HARN_StatePlane_New_Mexico_Central_FIPS_3002_Feet

Path Types :

Paved Multiple Use Trail - A paved trail closed to automotive traffic_Quetzel Greem.

Bike Lane - A portion of the street with a designated lane for bicycles_Moorea Blue.

Buffered Lane - Conventional bike lanes paired with a designated buffer space_Ultra Blue.

Bike Route - Cars and bicycles share the street Seville_Orange.

Bike Blvd. - A shared roadway optimized by bicycle traffic Anemone Violet.

Unpaved Multiple Use Trail An unpaved trail closed to automotive traffic_Topaz Sand.

NMDOT Facility - A Bicycle facility Owned and Maintained by NMDOT with different design standards than CABQ_Peony Pink.

Crossing- Bicycle or pedestrian under/over crossings_ Solar Yellow.

Hiking Trail - An unpaved trail open to foot traffic only_Cartographic Line.

Status:

Existing - Any physically existing facility where the construction is complete. Displayed as a solid line.

Proposed - Any facility that is identified in the Long Range Bicycle Plan or the Bikeways and Trails Facility Plan. Displayed as a dashed line.
dataIdInfo.idPurp:
The BikeAndWalkways FeatureClass is an ongoing comprehensive network of bike and walkway systems centered on the Albuquerque area. Data for this network of crossings, roads, and trails is gathered from City of Albuquerque data as well as provided information from neighboring entities.
***Note: this featureclass consists of both existing and propsed infrastructure.***
